%S A396472 0,0,1,2,0,3,1,2,5,0,3,6,1,4,7,2,10,5,0,8,3,11,6,1,9,4,7,15,2,10,18,5,
%T A396472 13,0,8,16,3,11,19,6,14,1,9,17,4,12,20,7,28,15,2,23,10,31,18,5,26,13,
%U A396472 0,21,8,29,16,3,24,11,32,19,6,27,14,1,22,9,30,17,4,25,12
%N A396472 Irregular triangle read by rows: row n lists a permutation of the nonnegative integers in the interval [0, A001911(n)] (see comments).
%C A396472 _Richard Stanley_ builds what he calls the Fibonacci array F (Stanley, 2024) or Fibonacci triangle poset (Stanley, 2021), where the labels of the edges of the resulting diagram determine the terms of the present sequence: T(n,k) is the sum of the edge labels along a downward path from the top of the diagram to the corresponding vertex. All edge labels are Fibonacci numbers. See Stanley links for details on how the diagram is constructed and labels assigned.
%C A396472 Row n has length A000071(n+3).
%C A396472 See also A396471.
%H A396472 David A. Corneth, <a href="/A396472/b396472.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10925</a> (first 17 rows flattened)
%H A396472 David A. Corneth, <a href="/A396472/a396472_1.gp.txt">PARI program</a>
%H A396472 Richard P. Stanley, <a href="https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2101.02131">Theorems and Conjectures on Some Rational Generating Functions</a>, arXiv:2101.02131 [math.CO], 2021 (see chapter 3).
%H A396472 Richard P. Stanley, <a href="https://www.gathering4gardner.org/g4g15gift/ExchangeArchive-FibArray-G15-087-1.pdf">A Fibonacci Array</a>, in Gathering for Gardner 15 Gift Exchange Book, 2024 (see chapter 5).
%e A396472 Triangle begins (see links for the explanation of the diagram):
%e A396472 .
%e A396472   Row n = 0 -------------------- 0
%e A396472                                 / \
%e A396472                               0/   \1
%e A396472                               /     \
%e A396472   Row n = 1 ---------------- 0       1
%e A396472                             /|       |\
%e A396472                            / |       | \
%e A396472                          2/ 0|      2|  \0
%e A396472                          /   |       |   \
%e A396472                         /    |       |    \
%e A396472   Row n = 2 ---------- 2     0       3     1
%e A396472                       /|     |\     /|     |\
%e A396472                     0/ |3   0| \3 0/ |3   0| \3
%e A396472                     /  |     |  \ /  |     |  \
%e A396472   Row n = 3 ------ 2   5     0   3   6     1   4
%e A396472                  5/|0 5|\0 5/|0 / \ 5|\0 5/|0 5|\0
%e A396472                  / |   | \ / | /5 0\ | \ / |   | \
%e A396472   Row n = 4 --- 7  2   10 5  0 8   3 11 6  1   9  4
%e A396472                                 ...
%e A396472 T(n,k) = sum of edge labels along a downward path from the top of the diagram to the corresponding vertex.
